+# Discover reusable Discourse components
+
+Search before creating a visible component. Prefer official, current, source-backed evidence.
+
+## Search order
+
+1. Inspect the running site's settings, theme components, and relevant route.
+2. Inspect the target Discourse source and theme API for native behavior.
+3. Search the repository for an existing implementation.
+4. Search the official [Theme Component category](https://meta.discourse.org/c/customization/theme-component/120) on Discourse Meta.
+5. Search the [Discourse GitHub organization](https://github.com/discourse?q=theme-component&type=all&language=&sort=updated) and the component's source repository.
+6. Search recent official Meta announcements and developer guides for the feature or extension point.
+
+Useful search terms combine the surface and intent, for example:
+
+- `site:meta.discourse.org/c/customization/theme-component sidebar blocks`
+- `site:github.com/discourse discourse theme component banner`
+- `site:meta.discourse.org transformer topic list Discourse`
+
+## Qualify a candidate
+
+Inspect the source instead of relying on a screenshot or topic title. Record:
+
+- official or community ownership;
+- last meaningful update and recent compatibility activity;
+- supported Discourse version and release channel;
+- modern `.gjs`/theme API usage rather than deprecated template overrides;
+- settings, locales, accessibility, responsive behavior, tests, and documentation;
+- conflicts with the parent theme or other enabled components;
+- whether it supplies behavior, presentation, or both;
+- how much of the approved requirement it covers without invasive overrides.
+
+Prefer a maintained official component that covers most of the requirement and exposes useful settings. Do not install a component only because its name resembles a design region.
+
+## Return an inventory, not a link dump
+
+| Requirement | Core/native option | Existing theme option | Official component | Coverage | Compatibility | Recommendation |
+| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |
+| Right rail modules | inspect sidebar/block APIs | none found | candidate + source link | high/medium/low | verified/unknown | reuse/adapt/build |
+
+Label a result `not found` only after the official category and GitHub source search. Label it `not verified` when network access or target-version source is unavailable.
+
+## Current examples, not default choices
+
+- [Right Sidebar Blocks](https://meta.discourse.org/t/right-sidebar-blocks/231067) demonstrates configurable sidebar composition.
+- [Versatile Banner](https://meta.discourse.org/t/versatile-banner/109133) demonstrates a reusable banner component.
+
+Treat these as examples to evaluate, not automatic dependencies. Confirm their current source and compatibility at implementation time.
+
+## Avoid stale or risky reuse
+
+Reject or escalate a candidate that depends on deprecated `.hbs` template overrides, unscoped DOM mutation, deep selectors, undocumented core internals, abandoned code, or an incompatible release range. Forking a component transfers upgrade and accessibility ownership to the project; record that cost explicitly.
