+# Figma or image to Discourse surface
+
+Use this process for PNG, JPG, WebP, or PDF exports when direct Figma access is unavailable.
+
+## Request an implementation packet
+
+Ask for the smallest coherent packet for one route:
+
+- one full-page desktop export at the intended viewport size;
+- one full-page mobile export;
+- close crops of dense or ambiguous regions;
+- prototype notes or a short screen recording for interaction;
+- typography, colors, spacing, icons, and downloadable assets;
+- component states and variants;
+- the route name, user role, sample data, and expected behavior.
+
+Prefer 1x PNG for layout review and SVG for approved vector assets. Use PDF for multi-frame review, not as the only source of exact asset dimensions. Do not copy text or icon shapes from a raster image when source assets exist.
+
+## Build the design-to-surface map
+
+Before code, create or update `docs/FIGMA_DISCOURSE_MAP.md` if that document exists in the repository. Otherwise return the map in the plan.
+
+| Design region | Discourse route/surface | Native candidate | Data/behavior | States | Decision | Evidence/question |
+| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |
+| Header | topic list header | core header | search, user menu | anon, member, mobile | retain + style | inspect target version |
+
+Use concrete names after inspecting the running site or source. Do not guess internal component names.
+
+## Read a static design cautiously
+
+Classify each observation:
+
+- **Explicit:** visible or specified in the design.
+- **Native:** behavior already supplied by Discourse and retained.
+- **Assumption:** plausible but unconfirmed.
+- **Missing:** a required state or interaction not supplied.
+
+Stop only when a missing answer changes architecture, data ownership, permissions, or destructive behavior. For minor visual gaps, state a reversible assumption and continue.
+
+## Compare accurately
+
+Match the design viewport and browser zoom. Compare in this order:
+
+1. page structure and content order;
+2. container widths and responsive behavior;
+3. typography and wrapping;
+4. spacing and alignment;
+5. colors, borders, shadows, and imagery;
+6. interactive and accessibility states.
+
+Do not chase pixel differences caused by different sample content, font loading, scrollbar width, or browser rendering until those inputs match.
+
+## Useful progress without complete designs
+
+When designs are incomplete, safely implement or document:
+
+- repository and token architecture;
+- typography and brand asset loading;
+- compatibility range;
+- route and component inventory;
+- extension decision records;
+- testing harness and system-spec setup;
+- a screenshot review checklist;
+- reusable settings and locale structure.
+
+Avoid speculative page layout, navigation restructuring, hidden native controls, or custom markup that may conflict with later frames.
